# FitUp — Redesign: Core Focus

## 🎯 Objective
Refocus the app around a **single, addictive daily competition loop**:
> “Am I winning or losing today vs my opponent?”

Optimize for:
- Instant clarity (≤ 3 seconds)
- Daily habit formation
- Clean, Apple-featured-level UX

---

# 🧠 Core Product Principles

- One primary focus per screen
- One dominant action per session
- Hide complexity, don’t remove it
- Competition > wellness
- Daily loop > long-term analytics

---

# 🏠 HOME (Primary Screen) — REDESIGN

## Goal
Make Home feel like a **game screen**, not a dashboard.

## Structure

### 1. Hero Match (80% of screen)
- Large circular gauge
- Show:
  - Step difference (e.g. `+193`)
  - Status: `YOU’RE WINNING` / `LOSING`
- Subtext:
  - Opponent name
  - “Ahead by X steps”

### 2. Dynamic CTA (Required)
- If winning → “Keep your lead”
- If losing → “Walk X steps to take the lead”

### 3. Secondary Matches (Optional, small)
- Label: “Other Battles”
- Compact list:
  - Opponent + +/- value only
- No charts, no extra data

---

## REMOVE from Home
- ❌ Readiness
- ❌ Sleep
- ❌ Charts
- ❌ Deep stats
- ❌ Multi-section scrolling
- ❌ “Competition Edge Today” wording (simplify to “Today”)

---

# ⚔️ MATCH SYSTEM

## v1 Rules
- Steps ONLY (no calories)
- 1 primary visible match
- Multi-match supported (background), but not equally surfaced

## Multi-Day Matches
- Keep internally
- Surface:
  - “Day X of Y”
  - Daily win/loss
  - Match score (e.g. 1–0)

---

## DO NOT ADD (YET)
- ❌ 2v2 matches
- ❌ Team battles
- ❌ Match types (calories vs steps)

---

# 📊 STATS TAB (Replace Health Tab)

## Goal
Simple, addictive, brag-worthy stats

## Show ONLY:
- Win rate (%)
- Total matches
- Current streak
- Top rival (most played)
- (Optional) Total steps in matches

## Avoid:
- ❌ Complex breakdowns
- ❌ Over-analysis
- ❌ Multi-graph screens

---

# 🏆 LEADERBOARD

## Structure

### Friends Tab (Primary)
- Weekly ranking (Mon–Sun)
- Sorted by total steps
- Only users with data shown

### Global Tab (Secondary)
- Same logic, all users

---

## Empty State
- “No data yet — start a match”
- CTA: Invite / Challenge

---

# 🔔 NOTIFICATIONS (CRITICAL)

## Required Triggers

- “You just got passed by [Name]”
- “You’re 150 steps away from winning”
- “You won today”
- “Final day — you’re ahead”
- “New challenge from [Name]”

## Notes
- Drive urgency + emotion
- Avoid spam
- Tie directly to match state

---

# 🚀 ONBOARDING

## Goal
User in first match within **< 2 minutes**

## Flow
1. Enter name
2. HealthKit permission
3. Immediately:
   - Start bot match OR
   - Prompt to invite friend

## Remove:
- ❌ Multi-step explanations
- ❌ Delayed match start

---

# ⚠️ CRITICAL FIXES (Pre-TestFlight)

- Fix duplicate match cards
- Fix WINNING / LOSING logic
- Fix missing data (“--steps”)
- Sync stats across screens
- Ensure leaderboard not empty/broken

---

# 💰 MONETIZATION

## Strategy
- Free: 1 active match
- Paid: multiple matches

## UI Rule
- Always emphasize ONE primary match

---

# 📱 APP STRUCTURE

## Tabs

1. Home
   - Primary match focus

2. Battles
   - All matches + history

3. Stats
   - User performance

4. Leaderboard
   - Weekly rankings

5. Profile
   - Settings / subscription

---

# ❌ DO NOT BUILD (YET)

- Rewards / badges / streak systems (beyond simple streak)
- Chat / messaging
- AI recommendations
- Calories tracking
- Deep analytics
- Social feeds

---

# 🧩 SUCCESS METRICS (TestFlight)

- Time to first match < 2 min
- % users who complete 1 match
- % users who return next day
- % users who invite a friend
- Daily opens per user

---

# 🧠 FINAL PRINCIPLE

> This is not a fitness tracker  
> This is a **daily competition game**

---

# 🏁 SUMMARY

Focus on:
- Clarity
- Simplicity
- One core loop

Defer:
- Complexity
- Expansion
- Feature depth

---

# 🔑 NORTH STAR

> “Make it the easiest and most addictive way to compete with one friend on steps, daily.”